\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Could you tell me your name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Elizabeth Anne Metcalf. Is that the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  name you went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Can you tell me your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I live at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}10 Hunts Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And you're a widow I know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Can you tell me the year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ? 18 - 1896.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh - I've forgotten that - I was twenty three nearly ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No the year you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh - well I was twenty-three when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  in 1896 so we'll have to work that backwards - I never thought - I never thought that up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Can you tell me where you were born - the house you were born in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Eh now then - I was born in the Height - er - a little cottage at the bottom of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Clarement Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember the name of the place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 It was on the main road
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You don't remember the name though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I think it - it would be a high number because - er - it was - practically the last row of cottages I should say that was in the high then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Can you tell me how many years you lived in the house where you were born - do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - no I couldn't say because - me father was a coachman to a gentleman in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Swinton{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Park{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Not at Teapot Hall by any chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, not Teapot Hall - no, it was a house called Spring Wood, and I think when I was quite young the gentleman had 
to reduce all his - he lost a lot of money, I think, that was the trouble, from what I've heard father and mother talk about, er father came out of work just then and mother was having her third baby. And - er I think we left the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13789483\charrsid9916195 He}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ight and father got a place as horsekeeper to the Salford Corporation. And we had to remove down to near {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Regent Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Ordsall Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - no we didn't live at - it was a little square where we lived and there only six houses up one side of it and it was called {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Trafalgar Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Where did you live the longest though - at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Clarement Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Trafalgar Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh I think I lived - I must have lived at Trafalgar Square longer than I lived really at the Height - then - but I came back to the Height you know thirty-four or five years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you live at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Trafalgar Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 until you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I lived there to - oh I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  there and I lived there with - er - me father and mother - I never left home because I was the youngest and the only girl and all the four boys were all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I'd only the four brothers. Never had any sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You told me your father was forty-one when you were born and your mother was thirty-nine, can you tell me where your father came from?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes, they came from - er - believe it was - er - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Warrington Way{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - Stratton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And you told me he looked after horses - did he always look after horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He worked - worked on a farm for his sister until after they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  - until after the eldest brother was born and then of course he got a place as a what they called a pad groom in those days to old Mrs Greenhaulgh of Walton Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Where's Walton Hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Warrington{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What is a pad groom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well it's - it's a gr
oom - under groom that's - er - if they lady of the hall or the house wants to go out riding the pad groom follows her always on another pony. That's the idea - that's what I've always understood. And me father - me dad - I always called him dad - he - er
 - he was among horses all his life - he loved horses and he - had he been able to be educated he'd have made a splendid vet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he do any casual or part time jobs apart from looking after horses - his full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh he - he was over all the horses in the corporation yard - was about sixty or seventy horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And he continued this until he died at the corporation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 The last two years he had - the last two years he didn't really do much work but we had to live in the house. It was a ho
use that went with the job, you see, and we had a wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13789483\charrsid9916195 [\'85]e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  through our house - down the cellar into the corporation yard - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So you could go and see the horses as a girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh he went night and day - sat up all night sometimes with a sick horse. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you go and look at the horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I've lived amongst them.
