\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 They - the - the front bedroom was a very big room - it was bigger than this room I think and .....
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who had that - your mum and dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No - the boys had it. They'd two beds in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Your mother and dad had the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And father and mother had the middle bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And you being the only girl got the little room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I got the little back room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 We had - well we bathed in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - I think me dad used to bath me about every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How often did you have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Every week. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Can you tell me where the family had their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about on Sundays or special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well in the front room on a very, very special occasion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And what would you call a special occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - no - the - we used to sometimes think we'll have our tea in the parlour. Now and again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did she have a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh it was a little kitchen grate for a good many years and then - er - they put us a small range in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What kind of a range - was it gas or was it coal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh coal - coal. B
ut with - er - we got a lot of tim - wood out of the corporation yard - er - they had - er - a wheelwrights shop in the corporation yard you know where the - repaired all their own carts - they had wheelwrights there - working and a smithy. And we used to
 - they used to - if they'd an old cartwheel the wheelrights'd - one of the wheelwrights'd run round to our cellar door and throw the - the wheel - part of the wheels in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Can you tell me when breakfast was eaten? Did you all have it together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh 
well, me father used to do - go round the stables in the morning about half past seven to eight to see the carters were in - the men - you see - the - and then he - er - he'd come in have his breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And did you all have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - my mother and him had their breakfast together - of course the lads got grown up and they'd gone out to work I suppose.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When you were children your mum and dad had it together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I had me meals with them when I was there - when I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And what about your brothers - did they have it all together with mum and dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh they'd got theirs as they wanted I suppose. I know mother used - in the winter mother used to make porridge at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did she make for breakfast - what would you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
And er - put it in pound pot - put it in pound jam jars and put it in the even all night and it was warm in the morning. In a kitchen and - er - the lads used to get their own out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you always have porridge for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I didn't. Sometimes I did. I do - well I do now, but sometimes I did and sometimes I - I just had what I wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have something special on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. I know me father and mother used to have bacon. I tell you what they used to have - cheese and bacon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have cheese and bacon with them on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So - if I wanted it I could have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 The boys too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - they had what they wanted - they got what they wanted - they - while mother was laid up wi
th that bad leg - bad foot - well both feet in fact - er - it got them that they got what they liked you see, whatever they fancied, they looked after themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Can you remember what you had for dinner - at mid-day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh well - we had all sorts - we always had a dinner. I know that. Well we always had a real - potato dinner. We always had a dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Anything special on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh a roast. A joint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What kind of joint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh it was - we had a real joint for Sunday - it did - it di
d Sundays dinner and supper at night - they had cold meat for their supper I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did they have for their teas - do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - I don't know - there's nothing particular. Jam - we'd home made jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Your mother made her own jam then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your father or mother make their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Not every week but many a time she did bake. Oh yes. But she didn't - she didn't reckon to bake certain days you know, like Sunday. Yes, well perhaps mother would bake one we
ek twice and then another week she might not bake at all, but, of course while she was laid up with her foot she couldn't bake at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did she bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I did I bottled fruit. I have done.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 That was in your marriage - but did your mother ever do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No, I don't think she ever bottled fruit. I tell you what she used to do - always plenty of pickles. Oh yes, always had - we always had plenty of pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did she make wine or medicine at all? Or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your mother or father grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh we'd no garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they buy a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well we had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Buy them? Oh there was none in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they keep any livestock - with having a stable next to the house - were you able to keep any livestock for the family - hens or pigs?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - mother - mother'd got - she'd got a few hens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Just about a dozen hens and we had the eggs you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well she used to feed them. And they - er - roosted in our cellar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So you used to go down to the cellar to collect the eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How many times a week did you eat meat - do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - we had a joint Sunday and it used to last til about Tuesday. It was - a - oh yes it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have any other kind of meat other days - did you have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - I know mother bought rabbits at the door
. There was a woman used to come round with the - er - rabbits bought many a couple of rabbits for one and three and one and four. One and three and one and four for a couple.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever get any meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no. Not there - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you ever remember seeing your mother have less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your father have more than anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 We - we never were short of food - I thank God for that. We were - never - never shor
t of - we didn't live rich - we were never short of food - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh - I don't think they bothered.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have whatever you were given?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh we had to have what was got for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And were you allowed to leave anything on the plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't think - I don't think lads ever did leave anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever leave anything on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't know. No, I don't know that I ever - I used to have just what - a little bit that I wanted then I'd done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
If there was something on the table that you wanted - like the salt - could you ask someone to pass it or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, we used to say - well they could reach it for themselves if they wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh many a time the lads did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain w
ay at the table - were they strict on table manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh they - we just learned to use a knife and fork and - and it ended there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When could you leave the table - did you have to wait until you were told or could you leave when you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
I think - I think the lads got - got that they got up when they'd finished and they'd clear their own plate and knife and fork a spoon, whatever they had, they'd carry it in the scullery but they wouldn't wash it you know. They just cleared it away.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did all the family sit at the table for meals and did you all have a particular place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No, we just - er - sit round the - round the table. I think me dad - mother and dad had their own places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you all sit down at the table together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 If they were in and the meal was there they'd sit down together. I think we had - we always had Sunday dinner together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who served the meal? And what order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Me dad always carved. He always carved the joint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who actually served the rest of the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He was a good carver - he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember who served the rest of the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I think mother put - would put the vegetables out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did she serve it in any order - did anyone ever get served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I think she'd serve the eldest one first.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Not dad? Just the eldest boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, no, no, she wouldn't serve dad first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember as a baby - do you remember anything about sitting in a different chair when you were tiny? And who fed you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - no, I - I don't know - but - well, I - no, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was your mother easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well she had more - mother had more go in her than me dad had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was she easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well she wouldn't let you have all your own way. She'd argue a bit with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did she show affection? Was she affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I couldn't call her really affectionate although she never was unkind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 If you had worries could you take them to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I could - not with me mother like I could with me dad. Oh I could do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was he easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh he was easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was he affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Very. Very affectionate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did they expect you to behave towards them? Did you have to behave in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, - er - if there was anything to be said me mother said it and I can always remember her telling our - our lad - I call him our lad - I can always remember her saying get on with your - get on with you and let your meat stop your mouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your parents teach you to behave towards your brothers in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. No. No. The boys - I think the lads - like - looked on me as a baby sort of - with being the only girl. I don
't think really - one moment, mind me - I don't think she wanted me. I don't think she did. Well she'd had four boys. And I don't think she wanted any more because they weren't well off - father and mother weren't well off at all - although I - we never w
anted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What made you feel she didn't want you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I think she had - I think she felt she'd had enough with four lads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you notice this or something that made you feel this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - no. No, I think - er - I don't know. She was - she was a 
bit more - er - firm than me father was - I think that's were how we were - would be put on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 If a child hit you outside were you taught to hit it back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - no, she wouldn't say that - but she wouldn't pet me or anything like that. No, she would
n't - she wouldn't pet me. Now me dad would, oh yes, he would. Well it was with me being the little girl I think and I always remember the night you know I had two - two daughters - and the night before the young one was born and he'd been - bad - er - th
r
ee months - he had gangrene in one foot - he was eighty-two you know - and - er - I bathed his foot for him in Condyle fluid - that's what we had to do in - then - and I sat with him - I fed him with his supper - he had bread and milk - I always remember 
it and I sat with him with his arm through mine and he got hold of me hand - he says, "thank you Lizzie for all you've done for mum and me, he says, God'll never let you want." And that - the next morning my youngest girl was born and it was Good Friday.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So you knew that your dad was pleased to have you didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Do you remember what your parents used to think - did they hope you'd grow up in a certain way? Did they bring you up to think that certain things were important do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
I can always remember me mother saying as I grew up - now it wasn't because I was outward goers or anything of that - but she always said if I brought any trouble home - if I got into any trouble I musn't come home with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What else did they consider was important. What did they teach the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well the eldest - the eldest one - he got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  - he was only about twenty-one when he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  and then the next }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11862198\charrsid9916195 one he went in the Marine Auxili}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ary and he was sent abroad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But do you remember what they said was right and wrong? Anything that they used to say now that's wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh - oh mother and the lads - I think - had plenty of arguments - she used to say "Rights right and wrongs wrong and wrongs no ones right." Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no. We never heard that language - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 If you did something your parents didn't like what happened were you punished and who punished you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, well, I don't know that we did do anything really wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You never remember being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Never got a walloping or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. I had a fairly happy childhood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You don't remember being punished on any occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh - only once. I'd gone out to the Sunday school and I've gone up to see some people that used to live next door to us and they kept me from me tea and me mother didn't know where I was - and she sent me youngest brother -
 she thought of these people and she sent me youngest brother and - I think she walloped me when I got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your dad ever wallop you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No. No, never, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who do you think had the most impression on you? Who taught you what was mo
st important in life? Did you get the ideas from your mother and father or was your mother more important or your father more important in teaching you what life was about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, because we never saw anything wrong done in the house, you see, they didn't use bad language and we never saw any nasty ways.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When you had a birthday would be different from any other day? Would you get a present or have anything special to eat or have friends in?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - no, I - I think they used to buy me bits of thi
ngs I think, when I was little I'll tell you what I do remember - one birthday - I'd be about eleven I think - eleven years old. And I took about twelve of the girls in my}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11862198\charrsid9916195  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 class home with me for tea and I never told me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh - me mother told 'em she says well, she says, I couldn't make you all a party because I didn't know - she says, so you'll all have to have an egg each. She borrowed a dozen eggs - they had to have eggs and bread and butter - there was no cake. Oh she l
ived - and that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever have a party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I had a birthday party when I was eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Can you remember doing anything special with your mother and father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh well - well - right time at Christmas - always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well - you see me father got plenty things given to him - in the food line at Christmas - and I've seen hung up in our cellar - I've seen a hare - couple of rabbits a turkey a goose - it was the farmers that supplied the corporatio
n with er - different things - hay and corn and stuff for the horses, and they always sent - well, two of them - used to bring a hamper every Christmas with perhaps a turkey in and - or a - a goose and onions, apples, sage, parsley, all round, right big h
ampers, you know. And then the vet that was with - real vet for the horses he always sent a big round of beef. Oh we - had - we had - well, never short of food, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was there anything special you did in the way of games or did you go to church or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Not particular - no. I never wanted to go to Sunday school parties. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have any musical instruments in the house? Did anybody play an instrument at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well we had nothing in the - oh me second brother played a cornet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he play this at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Mother used to bless him and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did anyone sing in the home? Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - no, nobody sang - only me mother. She could sing. But they were all hymns
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You didn't have family sing-songs together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No, we didn't because - well, I don't know why - of course when the lads got going out you know they didn't bother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your parents ever play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh we used to play dominoes. We never - we didn't - not til after I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  - er - they never played cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they play any games outside with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no. Because mother was crippled and all - they didn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes. Yes. We had books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh they always took - they used to take the Evening News - ha'penny and they took the - er - Pembleton Reporter. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was it going then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes, it must have been - we had the Reporter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Er - no me dad didn't - couldn't read much - I told you - he - he'd really no education. But she could read and she used to read the Evening News every night to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did she read to you too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Do you remember a funeral in the family and who attended and what type of clothes did they wear. Can you tell me anything about a family funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh well, I don't know that we had any - only - er - no I don't remember. I had an uncle lived 
in Pembleton and - er - his wife died - his second wife it was - and I can remember me mother saying that - er - there were toll bars you know in those days - on the way like - she wanted to be buried - me aunt did - at - I didn't know her - it was - like
 I was too young to know her - and she wanted to be buried at Daresbury where she'd come from and - er - in Cheshire - Daresbury and me mother sent me eldest brother to sit with the driver of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4542623\charrsid9916195 ho}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 rse and gave him money to pay at these toll bars as they went along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were children allowed to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh we didn't go - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your mum and dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh they went. Or perhaps only me brother went and me dad. I don't know - I think me mum'd go - I don't think so. But she said she gave our John money to pay for the tolls at the different toll bars on the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He went by horse or something did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
He drove with - he sat with the driver of the hearse. Yes it went from Pembleton. Me uncle that buried - that was burying his wife - he was one of t
he first founders really. Well in - him and a few more started the - got together and - er - I don't know where they bought the goods - whether they went to Rochdale - you know - to .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Why Rochdale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, that was where the Co-op first started you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And they started the Pembleton one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
And he was on the committee - he was one of the committee - the - there was five or six men that worked in Pembleton in the Mills and - er - he was among them - and they decided they'd begin and bu
y for their own families and buy wholesale you see - and then they got one or two customers and - er - eventually they began to - I think they got a little shop - empty shop - or something - and they used to go and make all the stuff up at night after the
y'd been at work all day - they'd go different nights and - er - make the - like rice and sugar and tea. There was no packets in those days - I don't think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Butter and everything was served loose wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they eventually give up the mill and just run the Co-op?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh - oh no he never - he didn't give up the mill. Oh no, he was the mill related to silk mill in Lissadel Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 It wasn't R.K. Armitages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, that was cotton, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was it Wright Turners, were they silk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No, it wasn't Wright Turners but it was in - in Lissadel Street - the mill - they called it the silk mill and he was the millwright there. And he was one of the first on the committee that they - they formed a committee - and then they go
t - er - a little shop - and then they got - er - a youth to run errands and that and take bits of orders out I suppose and it grew that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So when I draw my divi I've got your uncle to thank for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't know. But there's no Pembleton Co-op now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were you ever taken visiting friends or neighbours or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No, I don't think - no - you see, me dad and me mother - I don't think they mixed up a lot you know, where we lived - where we had to live at Trafalgar Square it was a very 
poor area round there - there was a lot of poverty - a lot of poverty - I wouldn't like it to be so again. I can - I can remember it - and I can remember a woman - and mother was very good, she used to send me out many a time with a meal to - er - differe
n
t people that she'd heard of - had nothing to eat and she sent me when I was a - a little girl to this - er - woman - she had four children and her husband had left her and - er - she lived in one room - that was that was all - one room - did everything i
n
 it and I took this and she said - she told me - she said - er - ah well, she says, you can eat in street but you can't sleep in street. She said, and if I can go out and do a bit of work and get enough to pay for room - rent a room she says I don't care.
 Oh there was a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You mean people actually starving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 They were really - they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Because there was a great deal of unemployment was it at that time - wasn't there a lot of work even in the mills round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I don't k
now because I never had anything to do like with - er - with - er - I know - I can remember one winter and it was a very long cold winter and there was - er - no - well we bought coal you know in hundred weights then, you didn't get - you had to get a loa
d
 - but this winter it was very cold and there was a lot of poverty about and - er - me father - he went to different shopkeepers on Regent Road and he got promises of scrap meat, bacon, bones, you know, lamb bones and all sorts of things - peas, beans and
 
of course he had carrots and turnips and the yard for the horses and oatmeal - he got some oatmeal from promised him and a baker promised some bread and me mother set to and she made soup in our wash-boiler - in the cellar. And then - er - me father had a
 
very big iron boiler in the - one of the places - for the horses - that he used to make gruel for the horses - and he cleaned it all out and they made soup in this - er - big boiler and I can remember seeing the people come - they had to come on a certain
 
time at a certain day twice a week - they came for two or three weeks that winter and me mother gave them soup. They had to bring their own - utensils whatever they wanted and - and she made soup two or three times a week. And they - they used to come in 
t
he corporation - they let them in the corporation yard to come across and bring their own jugs or whatever they had - were all sort of things came. They was - they was that hungry and they were there for - you know the children running about barefoot. Eve
n in the cold. Oh it was terrible. I'd never like to see them days again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 It was a poor district wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh it was. It was a very poor area. And yet you see we never wanted for anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You were probably the rich family of the district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 We must have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were you ever taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh - I used to go out - well - I used to go with me dad on Regent Road doing shopping. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever go anywhere else with your father apart from shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I used to go w
ith him to Shudehill to the wholesalers you know when he was buying for the corporation. Oh there was two - er - several big commission agents that knew him very well. 'Course he'd buy a couple of tons of swede turnips - a ton or two of carrots and they w
ere brought and then there was the flour mill up - er - Hope Street off Oldfield Road - er - the name was Aston I think - Aston }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703106 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
 Morse - and at Christmas they used to give me dad half a sack of flour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember any other outings with your parents - did you go away for Bank holidays or did you do anything special on Bank holidays?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No, I think - er - there was a man had a pony - a nice pony - and there was something wrong with it's teeth - and he'd had the vets to it but none of them did it a
ny good and he brought it to me dad. He was a grocer - he had a grocers shop in Chapel Street and - er - he brought this pony and he told me dad he said if you can cure it you can have it. Anyway, me dad and me youngest brother - he was growing up then - 
they drew some teeth at the back of its mouth - me dad saw what it was - it was these teeth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did they do it - did they have to tie the horse down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they have an anesthetic in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - no there was no anesthetic 
- and our Herbert - me brother - he held it - held its head up you know, while me dad got these teeth out and it came on like a house on fire after. Well - er }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11477661\charrsid9916195 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  who}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11477661\charrsid9916195  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
sits - the owner of it - her - er - he let me dad have it. Every weekend - and - er - he used to take me mother out a drive you know, we'd go to perhaps one of the farmers that he knew round Dunham and that way and I'd go with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And perhaps some Bank holidays you'd go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh - well - er - on a Sunday many a time we'd gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you go away for a holiday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, we never went to - not 'til we were real old you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You never went as a child with the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No, we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did you do on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I'll tell you what - what I can remember do
ing. Er - me brother - I had two friends - they were sisters - well they - these two girls, they were always falling out and I came in between them in age so I was like the peacemaker always. Well, me brother had two or three lads - friends - that on a Sa
turday our Herbert he used to get some - a lot of bricks and cover them with bird lime to catch sparrows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did he catch sparrows for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You'll laugh when I tell you. He always catch a lot of sparrows and he'd - er - pluck them - clean them - pl
uck them - him and me together - I helped him - me dad had a little room like he called his surgery where he kept all his horse medicines and things and we - he used to let us play in there and - er - our Herbert and me - we used to clean these sparrows a
n
d then we'd get me mother's roasting tin - big lump of dripping in it - and in this surgery there was a big range, you know, oh - and a big oven and range, and our Herbert'd make a fire and get the oven hot and we used to cook 'em. And then - these two gi
rls that were friends of mine - and the other lads that were pals of me brother used to come down Saturday at tea time and me mother'd make a big jug of tea for us and we had a tea party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did sparrows taste like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I've forgotten. I couldn't tell you now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And you always did that on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - many - many a Saturday we'd do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did you do on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - we didn't do anything really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You didn't do much on Sundays. Used to go - well - I got going to Christ Church on the Crescent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 That was Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh yes. And - er - well I went to the - er - Hulme Street day school you know, but - upper school they called it - it was the best school in Salford that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have special clothes for Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. We had - always had Sunday clothes to put on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were you allowed to play games or work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, no, no we didn't - we didn't play games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was it because your parents didn't like you playing games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No they didn't - they didn't really like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they attend a place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, St. Bartholomews Church - do you know it - off Oldfield Road - they started a Mission in Regent Street school - and me Dad started going there. Mother didn't go very much but she'd been brought up Adventist. Mother had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your dad go regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He went Sunday night - he used to go on a Sunday night 'til he like got - as he - he couldn't go really - he was infirm - got ......
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes I - I went to Hulme Street, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever go on Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - on - Whit week. Well we called the long trip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - er - a long - er - excursion into Wales.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did you go in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 By train - from Ordsall Lane station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What part of Wales would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh I've been to Llangollen - been to Barmouth - been to - er - Bangor with them and Llandudno. It was only a day you know. And of course when I was younger I've gone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11477661\charrsid9916195  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 with them to Worsley on the boat up the Bridgewater canal you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 That would be when it was all fields?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Rather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they have any other social activities organized by the church you went to and did you take part in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, there's nothing really that did happen because - I think - er - that Christ Church they were rather - narrow some way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Didn't have any sort of social side to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I didn't - no - didn't bother - I used to go to Sunday school and t
hen of course when I grew up and - I met me husband - well me husband - it was funny - how I met him. I met him at Pitney. No, it was one Sunday and - er - I'd got - me mother was staying with some - a distant relative at Pitney - at Winsham - a little pl
a
ce they called Winsham - and - er - I'd gone to see her one Sunday while she was there and - er - she'd been ill and she was staying there a bit and I'd gone to see her and - er - a girl friend with me and we went - we had a walk - we got off at Rostock -
 
Rostock railing station and we went and we had a walk and coming back were four young men on bicycles - and they asked us which was the way to the Red Lion. So I said well I said we're lost now. There were four lane ends and we didn't know which to take -
 
this girl - friend of mine and me and just then a gentleman came up in a trap and he was a doctor from Budworth and they asked him which was the way to the Red Lion - these young men and - er - he said carry on straight there. So I thought well if they kn
ow - get the way to the Red Lion that's the way we want to go so they walked with us and that's how - that's how I met him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But you didn't belong to the church choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they have a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no. Oh they were going to the Red Lion for their dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But I mean the church you went to did they have a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Christ Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Often in those days they had a temperance club and you had to sign the pledge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. I think - we had a Band of Hope at St. Bartholomews. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15826842\charrsid9916195 T}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 hen I was young - very young.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Not at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I always did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have family prayers in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I don't remember because it seemed as though things got broken up a lot when mother - having this accident with her feet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Tell me this story about your granny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well me grandma came to stay with us for a few weeks and - er - while she was there me mother persuaded dad - er - lik
e to take her to the pantomime. So - me dad - me dad worked to persuade her to go you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh so - well - they didn't - I think she was religious sort of with belonging to these particular Baptist - anyway - he got a cab and he - er - took
 her - and it was Bo-peep - little Bo-peep. Well, it started and when the ballet came on and there were dancing - you know, girls and - they'd be in tights - she says to me dad, she said - "Peter take me home." She said, "Take me home." He says it's only 
j
ust started mother. She said, take me home - I'm not standing here watch - I'm not sitting here, she says, watching them - er - dancing and kicking their legs about. That was it - kicking their feet about like - like - er - men - dressed like men in tight
s. She says, and wagging their big fat tails behind them. She says, the brazen hussies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 She'd never been to a theatre before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, she'd never been. They had to make their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you go to theatres or concerts when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No, I don't think I - I'll tell you where I used to go - you'll not remember the Hamiltons - Hamiltons panorama - they used to have it in the Free Trade Hall - and they showed - er - I think they were the orginators of the - of the pictures really because
 I was only young and - er - they went - it said }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15826842\charrsid9916195 H}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
amiltons Excursions around the world in a hundred and twenty minutes and they used to show pictures of all the world - Oh it were - they were nice. But what tickled us I don't know how they did it - there w
as like a little toy train used to go along the picture. Yes. I can remember it as well as anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You never went to music-halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And they gave - they gave us cheap tickets at school. Yes. Hamiltons Excursions around the World in a hundred and twenty minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And what was it showing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Different countries of the world and he had a pointer and he used to point out as though it was a big map. Which perhaps it was - I don't know. Like - er - sort of - er - well I don't know what it - 
what they were - they were pictures and - and - er - it was .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Still pictures or were they moving pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no - they were - they weren't moving - weren't moving characters - only the little train used to - and one - one land - it was at t
he foot of a sort of a mountain and it used to come across the picture and there was steam came from it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you ever remember going to a theatre while you were at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No - because - I went to Christ Church Upper School - and - they were a b
it on the puritan side I think - at Christ Church - on - it was on the Crescent you know - you'd remember that won't you - well I remember - it - er - it was - er - we paid you know - it was ninepence a week - school - oh yes. It was sixpence a week to 't
il you were - er - eight I think - eight years old - then ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How old were you when you started then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I was only - I'd be five, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What time of the morning did you start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you go to afternoon school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no we had a girls school and a boys school and they were separate - but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was it far away from where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well it was - over ten minutes walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You used to walk it did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh it was - quarter of an hour I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, me two brothers were there you see, they went - they were in the boys school - the two ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you come home for your meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, we came home for dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Yes - I didn't dislike it. But - er - this - er - we had a - a fresh headmistress came and - a Miss Law - and - er - I think she was sort of up-to-date and - er - she - well - she was very well educated and - er - I
 remember once - every year they had the prize-giving and concert - and the - the school - er - was divided with folding shutters, you know, from the boys - we were - the boys school and the girls - well every year these shutters were folded up to make th
e
 room big and all the Christ Church people used to come to the prize-giving and - er - of course we were trained like with special songs and that to sing for them during the prize-giving - and I always remember Miss Law, she got a few of us together and w
e
 had to cross hands like this and - well we - did this - was - we sang a song called see-saw. Well, we had to do all this and, do you know, the - the parishioners - the people - they didn't like it - they thought she was - that Miss Law was getting more t
o the theatrical side. Yes, they were that narrow. And I don't think - I think they told her not to have anything like that again - I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you like school though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, yes, I liked school - there was one teacher I - I couldn't get on with but she left and she went to the Isle of Man to a school there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But you liked the other teachers did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. I liked - I liked the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 This was a private school you say and you paid ninepence a week?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 If you were from - fi
ve years old I think 'til you were seven - six or seven - you paid sixpence a week and from then 'til you left school you paid ninepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And you were there all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did they particularly teach you about manners and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, yes, - er - very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did they teach you was important in life - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, they had - we opened with a hymn and - er - a prayer you know, every morning and - er - oh I don't know - we just had an ordinary
 education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But did they think certain things were important - like tidiness or punctuality or ways of speech?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I think - er - we paid a shilling a quarter for books. As - er - yes - it was ninepence a week and a shilling every quarter for books.
 They - we - they were never our own you know because every class we went into we left - that classes books behind us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And you paid for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were they particular about the way you spoke or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - I - they all
 seemed to be - all the pupils seemed to be - they weren't really the poor - they weren't from - now there was another - er - Chirst Church had three schools - they - that was called Christ Church Upper School - well they had a school in Hope Street - off
 Oldfield Road - Hope Street - now the - the poor went there a lot - a lot of very poor children - it was a poor area. Well then they had another school at .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they have to pay at Hope Street school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Now I don't know whether they paid a copper or - I wouldn't say - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have to go to school in those days though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh - I suppose they had to go. Oh yes, they had to go. And then they had another school at Windsor - they called it the New Windsor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were they very strict with you - if you did something wrong how did they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh yes - yes. Oh well, they used to give you a good - Miss Law - that was the headmistress - she - you got sent out to Miss Law she'd give you a severe talking to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Never punished in any other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh no. They all had canes but there was very little used I think. I don't know about the boys school. It was a Mr Roberts was the headmaster then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did you usually get in trouble for though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I don't - I never heard that anybody did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You don't remember if it was for anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no. No. Not ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were your parents interested in your schoolwork - did they visit the school and meet the teachers - were they interested in the school?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No, I never knew that they did. I don't think the teachers ever - or - ever encouraged it to take your parents in those days. No, I don't think they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were all the children from a similar type of home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I think they did - and I always remembe
r - the very first - er - bursary, they called it, was given while I was at school and it was a girl won it - how to - all Salford - they could all - er - school could send a pupil if they wanted - to the exam and it was a three year education at a school
 
that was on Deansgate at that time - they - er - Manchester Central - mm - well it was a girl from Christchurch won - won the very first that was offered in Salford - they called it a bursary - free bursary - and - er - her father and mother - they had - 
er - well her father was a plumber and he - they had their shop on Cross Lane they lived - where they lived - he was a master plumber - her father - and her name was Sarah Dabster - I always remember that. I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Can you remember if some children were picked out and treated differently from other - do you remember anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Only with that one teacher that I didn't like. I think she had favourites and I wasn't one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Why do you think she had favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I don'
t know - she seemed to pick on two or three of us some way. I don't know why - I don't know but we ever did anything wrong or - I remember on girl - er - taken ill at school - her - they were Higson the decorating at corner of - end of Liverpool Street - 
s
he was a lovely girl - and long hair - she fell flat on the floor in the classroom. Old Miss Law was in a shocking state. She sent me out to go to her home to bring her mother and she came her mother came back with me - and got a cab and took her home but
 she had a very bad attack of brain fever - she never came back to that school. When she got better they sent her to a private school that was up Eccles New Road somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever have gangs in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, at playtime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have people who ganged together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't think we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember any child being left out of anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't remember anything like that. We all seemed to - keep together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Would you have stayed longer if you could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I think - I perhaps could have done - I don't know whether I wanted to or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you go to evening classes or any other education once you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't think there was very much in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have any regrets about your education - did you think it was worthwhile? Did you benefit from it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh well, yes - I think - I think that - I remember I had two or three quarters in French. Now, Miss Law took that - 
the French class herself and I thin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11600113\charrsid9916195 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  that was her own per}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11600113\charrsid9916195 q}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 uitsite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11600113\charrsid9916195 (?)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
 because we had to pay half a crown a quarter extra for that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you enjoy that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I enjoyed it - I've forgotten what I got - I learned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you think you got some benefit from your education though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh yes, I - I think - er - and it was the class of school I went to and the - girls that were there along with me and none of them were - were very poor you know, none of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, he never did. He voted and that was about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He didn't talk about it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, of course she'd no vote. So - no - she had no vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But was she interested in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I - well
 - I used to hear her say to me dad - I think she was more Conservative than him - he was - er - he was a Liberal - honestly - and I heard me mother say - you know - she said - dad, Liber - Liberals are very narrow minded folk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Why did she think that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't know why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You remember your father voting though in an election do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh - he always voted - he - but he never told us who he voted for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He wasn't a member of a political party of anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Nor worked for them
? In those days you had a house that belonged to Salford Corporation - in those days often you had to vote a certain way or you lost your job or you lost your house if you didn't vote the way whoever was in charge wanted you to. Do you think your father e
ver had this trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't think so - no. No, I think that - er - he was left to choose for himself - that way. He never told anybody who he voted for.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 It did happen in those days didn't it that you had to vote for a certain person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, they always said you know - you know Gross }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13703106 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  Whitmore - Groves - James Groves - and - er - I know he put up for parliament you know - well he got in once - er - James - Mr James Groves it was - he got in and then when he put up again at the next elec
tion he didn't get in and they always said it was his own men that - got him out. Now whether it was so or not I don't know. Well I know it were said at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember when your parents weren't working what they did with their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Eh, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your mother have any interests outside the house? Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh - no. No - she didn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When your father got home from work in the evenings how many evenings a week did he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well they used to - me mother used to read the Evening News to him and - er - if there was any jobs to do in the house - like repairs - he used to do all the boot repairs and - er - he .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he go to any clubs or did he ever go to a pub for a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Very rarely. Or perhaps on a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your mum go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes. Saturday night they might just go on Regent Road and .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Or attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, he didn't because 
happen he'd work - well he worked - while he was very young. He had - he'd worked from being seven years old you know. He had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So he wouldn't have a lot of schooling then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. He hadn't. And I told you - had he had a good education he'd have made a splendid vet. He would. He loved horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he ever bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No, he didn't bet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember if they belonged to any kind of savings club like a boot club or a sick club or a funeral club in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh well - the - the - mother paid like insurance - only a penny a week. Funeral club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters - was there one of them - or anybody in the family you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, only the one - brother I had - the - the third - the third brother he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You felt very close to him did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And that - those are his daughters that are in there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did you get on with your older brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was there anyone else apart from your brother you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No. Well I had two friends that were sisters - I told you - and I came in between the two of then - they were always falling out. And I was the peace maker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who did you play with as a child - did you play with your brothers or did you play with neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, me youngest brother was five years older than me. So that - really - he was ten when I was only five you see and he had his - one or two - if they'd been at the corporation yard - or - the 
lads never went out to play very much - they went in the yard.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What games did you play then in the yard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, I don't know. They went down the cellar and in the yard and had a - was - er - looking at the horses and - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did you play as a girl - do you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11600113\charrsid9916195  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 remember any of the games you used to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I used to love to play with cups and saucers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were you allowed to get dirty if you were playing - did your mother worry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, I don't know that I ever did get very dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Could you play with anyone or were there certain children your mother didn't like you playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
I think that there was only one or two that lived just near to - but - you see there was only six houses where we lived. In that road - there was only six houses. And I - I don't know that there was many of them had - families - not children anyway.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But there were some that they didn't like you to play with - do you know why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, I don't know. No, I didn't - I never bothered - I never bothered about going out looking for friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you belong to a youth organ}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11600113\charrsid9916195 is}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
When I got - I started going to - Hulme Street Sunday School as well as the day school - er - there was a Miss Brapsdill and she used to have a Bible Class - I used - I used - I joined that. The Bible Class. She was a lovely lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have any hobbies? Did you keep any pets or collect things or did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, we didn't do anything like that - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You didn't do any gardening or collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever go fishing or anything like that? Or walks - did you go bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Not 'til I was - no I didn't. I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  before I - my husband had a bicycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But you didn't do it while you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I didn't do anything - well - no there was nothing like that when I was a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did I? It wasn't on. There - there was nothing then - that I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh a penny or two a week - that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And what did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 A penny. I used to - perhaps - if I could buy a little penny cup and saucer I was delighted - I was always fond of buying pots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your mother have any help in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Help? Er - well the woman used to do the washing when I was young. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did you call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh well, yes, yes, we had two or three like at different times. One - she was a very quiet little body - I can remember her - very thing and awfully 
quiet - and mother always used to call them up when dinner was ready - out of the cellar you know - she never would come and have her dinner - she wouldn't sit down with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Why I wonder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was she shy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 She - I think she must have been - she was very timid some way I - what I can remember of her. And - er - she did her work well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever have relatives who helped your mother in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Suppose your mother was ill or confined to bed - how did she manage then? Say when one of the children was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I was the youngest you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You don't remember anything about who helped her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I've heard me mother say when I was born that me eldest brother wouldn't look at me. And he - he t
old her - of course neighbours looked after them then - in those days you know when they were - your neighbours looked after the - mother - when they had a baby and I remember this neighbour I used to call her Mammy Cook. Up here she lived - they lived - 
a few - a door or two away from where we lived. And - she said to me eldest brother she said - eh Johnny, she says, aren't thou pleased that thee's got a little sister. He said - we could have done without her, he says, it's only another mouth to feed.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 This is why you always felt that your mum didn't want you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I - I don't know - I think she felt that she'd had enough with four lads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have any relatives living near to? And did you ever see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, they didn't - we had no relatives that lived near to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your parents have a lot of friends that they saw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Up here? Well, I suppose the lads played with other lads, I don't know. I never did because we left - we left the High you see and went down - had to go down ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But when you mum and dad lived in Salford did they have a lot of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about your mother? Did she have any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. She seemed to be friendly with everybody but - no particular friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they ever have friends into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well anybody that came was welcome. Nobody special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they have something to eat and a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. There was always something to eat for anybody that came.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they just have friends come in on special occasions or they could come in when they wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
I'll tell you what we - we used to have when our lads were young. I can remember this. You know the cattle market on Cross Lane - well, when I was young, there was a superintendant lived there - 
the house in the cattle market - the name was Brocklebank - and every - er - when pancake Tuesday - you know the - Monday was market day in the cattle market - and there were always plenty of cows and sheep and that well many a time the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11600113\charrsid9916195 er - Brocklebank's never bought}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
 any milk - there were always some cows there and it was giving milk - that the butchers used to go and buy their own you know, at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I remember the cattle being driven through the streets when I was a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. Well, 
- er - they came in on a Monday from - er - the butcher's - wholesale butchers used to go over to Ireland on a Sunday night and they'd buy their cattle on a Monday. Well, Monday night they came to - the market - here - and they - they were taken on the ra
ilway siding to the cattle market. Well, on a Tuesday the butchers used to go and buy their own - pick their own. And they weren't killed then - butchers'd buy them as they were - alive - very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And kill them themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes. Yes, they'd kil
l their own a lot - a lot of the butchers - at that time. And every - er - east - er pancake day - Brocklebank's - they had a big family - and they used to send - oh a great big tankard of milk down to our house - and me mother'd make batter and then on p
a
ncake Tuesday - all their lads - there was - how many - there was two - two lads - two sons and either three or four girls - and one of them was courting - there was - er - her boyfriends and they used to come down to our house and me mother made pancakes
. And they all had to throw their own up. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your parents go out visiting friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, they didn't no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 People say that they used to make their own amusements in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Say the Brocklesbanks or your brother's friends came in - how did you amuse yourself - did you make music or did you play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh they used to - go in the parlour - we called it - and have a sing-song.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What kind of songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh - now then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Never played games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't know whether they played dominoes - I never knew them to play cards. Never knew them not - but they may have played dominoes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember much about the different types of people in those days? The different classes or group
s? Before 1918, do you think that some people belonged to one social class and some people belonged to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't - I - don't think they did - perhaps some - er - some people felt they were a bit higher up than you were but - but those that
 were low down never seemed to try to ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What people would you say were the type that thought they were better than you were? What class do you think you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - I - I should think we were the - the working class I should think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What type of people were in the working class in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well I don't - er - I don't know. They were honest people - they worked for their living and - I don't think the - I don't think the people were always - wondering how they could make
 money. You know, whether they got it honestly or not - if they got a bit they got a bit - they were - no I don't think I was brought up among people - I never miexed - I tell you what - I never mixed up with the very poor only to - if me mother sent them
 a meal like you used to - where you took.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Did you notice a big difference in the homes between the people who had - say a decent job like your dad - and the poor people you used to take the food to - did you notice a big difference in the type of homes that they had? Do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No, they all seemed to have - er - clean, homely homes - not - er - fancy you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were you ever taught to treat one lot of people different to another? Were you ever taught to curtsey or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't think there was - not where I was anyway - not where I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever have to call anybody Sir or Madam? Do you not remember this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember anyone calling your parents Sir or Madam or showing them respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I - I don't think - I don't remember - anybody coming that said that. They used - er - say Mr and Mrs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember who were the important people in the district where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh there was the superintendant of the corporation yard - but ..... If he wasn't he felt he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He was the only one you remember that you considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I know - I know it were one superintendant that there was - and - I - it was after I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  - oh it was after Edna was th
ree or four years old - I had Edna and - er - I had - I was ill and when the doctor came I had diptheria - that was what was the matter with - so of course I had to be isolated. Well that - I - and the superintendant of the corporation yard he'd - been in
 the sanatorium - he'd had typhoid - mm - and - er - Ladywell - that was the sanatorium - no I didn't want to go because you see I lived at home - you know I told you with - we never left home when I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  and - er - I felt I - er - and so I was in be
d and me sister-in-law looked after me a bit and - and - I wanted them looked after - I wanted me - me dad and me mother to be looked after - I didn't mither about myself and another - another sister-in-law took Edna because Edna was only about four years
 
old. Their - their mother that are in there now - they took Edna - and - er - so long as Edna was looked after - me dad and my mother I didn't bother about myself and me husband - he had to sleep out - he wasn't allowed to stay because he worked among foo
d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did they keep you isolated then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I was in the bedroom - and a sheet over the door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they soak it in something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes. Er - disinfectant - carbolic - yes. Well - er - after I got better they came to examine all the drains 
you know - the health department and they found out something that the drains from our house weren't right - I don't know what it was - but where we lived in that square they had part of the square up to follow the drain - they were - they were - altering
 
the course of the - of the drain and I was going along the road - I was getting better - I was better then - And this superintendant was stood looking at the men that were digging - so he saw me and he came - he beckoned over there and I went to him. He s
aid - now look here Lizzie - he called me Lizzie - he said - look here Lizzie he says - look at the expense you're putting us to with having a sore throat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He didn't think it was serious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I suppose - oh - I says well I says if that's all the exp
ense I says - the ratepayers, that was it - look at the expense you're putting the ratepayers to through having a sore throat. Well I says anyway I says I had me sore throat at home and had a big doctors bill to pay - I says - I'm not like you - you went 
in sanatorium for nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember the shopkeepers in those days - who they used to mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No - I don't think the shopkeepers mixed with anybody really. Only their own customers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about the clergy? Who do you think they mixed with in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - the Minister at St Bartholomews was the - Mr Pethgate -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And who did he mix with - do you remember? Who were his friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't know who he had - because in the end he had to run away. Oh yes. Oh he had to run a
way for - he was - er - having trouble with boys - and he had to give it up and run.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about teachers - do you remember who teachers mixed with in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Teachers? Er - day school teachers? I don't know who they mixed with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about farmers - do you think they had their own particular friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Farmers? Oh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Or employers? No? What sort of people would you say went to church and what kind went to chapel - did you notice any difference in the types in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. I think they were just the people that lived round about that went - er - you know - reckoned to go to church and - or chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You didn't notice any difference in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I know - they used to go to - what they call Longford Hall in - 
er - off Regent Road there - at one time - there were - that seemed to get - er - people you know where churches didn't. People in - I think the people that - like the poorer people - sort of people - didn't like going to church - they thought they'd rath
er go to a mission. I don't know why. I think they had - they must have had a feeling - that they weren't quite as high up as the - I think the shopkeepers round St Bartholomews }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1641097\charrsid9916195 \endash }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1641097\charrsid9916195  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 went to church chiefly - the shopkeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you think that some people felt better than others though. Felt superior to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I think some did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What type of people - were they in certain jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I think - yes - I think they felt a bit superior you know some of them. Oh I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Just in certain types of job was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes - I think - I don't think some of them did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember the types of jobs these people were in the ones who felt superior?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you think there was a difference between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, perhaps - er - a qualified engineers - I think they felt better - you know - there were several engineering works in Ordsall Lane and I think that they felt - when they were - the - what they call fitters and that - they'd served their time to t
heir trade - I think they felt that they were a bit above the ordinary labourers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your mother and father both feel the same about people as a whole - whatever class they were in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. They didn't ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a certain class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No, never, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 If you were very poor and a lower class do you think you could move up in those days and better yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - I - you could do - but it was hard work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever know anybody who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't know - no, I don't think so. No, I can't recall anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Do you remember anyone being described as a real lady or a real gentleman in those days? Did you ever hear your mother or dad say she's a real lady or he's a real gentleman? And why do you think it was? What do you think they meant when they said that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't - I never heard them say it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember seeing a policeman where you lived as a child and what did you think of him? Did your mum used 
to say I'll tell a policeman if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh they used to be - make you fright - some people frightened their children - and say I'll bring bobby to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your mum do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember the police though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What were they like and how did they treat the people - do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I don't know that they - felt any better than anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you think they treated the people fairly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't think they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you think they were good to the people as a whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I - we never had anything to do with the police.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was your house rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 We paid a rent yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who was your landlord?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 It was the corporation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet in those days and how did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, they never really had to struggle but they never had too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was your dad never out of work - ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Not after we went with the corporation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Never had to ask for help from anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh no. But - in fact I don't know where he'd go - he'd have gone in those days for help. I suppose there were the Guardians - what they called the Guardians - but - er - I think what help they did
 give was - er - if a woman was went for help it was given sort of grudgingly I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Supposing someone did something that the neighbours didn't like do you ever remember how they showed their disapproval - were there any special things they did to s
how their disapproval? Say a woman was bad or a husband was bad - did they ever make dummies or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I used to hear them say sometimes that he - he knocks about and all that you know, I've heard ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did the neighbours show their disapproval about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't know. Never came across anything - because we - we'd never really mixed up with a lot of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When you were at school did you have a part time job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Me? No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When did you get your first full time job? How old were you when you got your first full time job? When you went out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I went - do you know where I went - I went in the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What job did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I went to - I was what they called a hank winder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What was hank winding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well it was - er - I didn't go - er - we lived in Ordsall Lane and this mill I went in was in Hulme. And it was a small wear mill - didn't weave calico then it was - they weaved tape and ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But what was hank winding actually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 It was - er - winding the - winding cotton on big bobbins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did you get the job - did your parents get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I went meself. Me father and mother didn't - never bothered about me going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What hours did you work in those days at the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - well - I was there 'til - er - well ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What time did you start in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Half past eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What time did you finish at night?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Six o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Long hours weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 They were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you work Saturday or Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes, Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But not a full day Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Half a day. Fifty-six hour - a - fifty-four or fifty-six hours a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you get holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you heck - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember what your wage was and how you felt about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Er - well - I got - er - for the bit - when first I went I only got seven shillings and then when I got - well - I - well they called a tertan loom - I got ten and then I got twelve. That was the most.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you think it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - it seemed to be general all round at - then - that kind of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And did you have to give it all to your mum in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, mother never - she said as long as I paid washerwoman that was all she wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So you paid the washerwoman out of your wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about your boss - how did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did you feel about him - did you like him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And you liked the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I liked the work - yes, I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You always found it interesting did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes, I liked - I liked the work because - it wasn't - er - sometimes it'd be fine cotton that I was - the han
ks - it was fine - very fine - just depended what he wanted for the work - for the looms you see and - er - sometimes it was course for - er - broad webbing - belting and that for the looms. 'Course I - I hadn't - never learned anything about weaving.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Would you have liked to have done some other type of job if you'd had the chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I don't know. No, I never - I never fancied dressmaking or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So you really liked your work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I liked - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have to serve an apprenticeship for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, you just went in and learned it - that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have to belong to a trade union in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I - I don't think there was any trade union then. Not - not in the mills.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you think there were any divisions of interest amongst the workers? Do you think some people felt one thing and some another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I - don't know, no, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Some people said there was a big division between trained craftsmen and other workers - did you think that in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Mind you - I think weaving was in - intricate work. In - in the mills where they did weave - cloth and stuff like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you think there was a big difference between the people who were trained and the people who weren't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I think - I think the mechanics thought they were somebody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When you went to work did it change your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No, it didn't change me at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And did you still live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 After I left school? Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did it change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Or with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, it didn't make any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you spend Sunday any differently when you started work? Did you still go to church or Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes - I - I went to church and Sunday school yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When you were working did you change the way you spent your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, when I got about - er - fifteen or sixteen - I used to go dancing a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, on a Saturday, that was all. Well, it was with friends I had and just went with them and ........
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I could take anybody home. But I never took any boys home. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have special friends at that time and where did you go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No, just kept on with our - I went to the Bible class - Miss Dabsters did the Bible class one night a week - I went to church Sunday night and Sunday afternoon I went to Sunday school. No, I didn't - er - didn't go wild at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your parents expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I - oh I had - oh they didn't let me be out late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they like to know where you'd got to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Can you tell me what age you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Twenty-three and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How long had you known your husband? I know you told me where you met him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Right out in the country. Never - never - try running - before I didn't know him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How long did you know him before you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh two - just over two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And where did he come from when you first met him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Where did he come from? Well he was - he was working - he worked at the co-operative store at - er - Pembleton - er - he was at Higher Halton -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So he lived in Salford just the same as you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Only he - he was in lodgings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have to save up money before you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh well, they were supposed to do, people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And did your parents help you to set up your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I never 
- I never left home you see and the only thing we did - we sort of refurnished the big bed - the front bedroom - that's all the furniture we ever bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - well when first I met him he never wanted - could only se
e him on a Wednesday night and a Sunday night, you know. And I was at work then - I worked then but he didn't - he didn't like me working you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you work after you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. Oh no, I left work be - soon after I knew him - knew Ted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have a big wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. Very quiet wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you get lots of presents and have a lot of guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes. We went to - we went to Matlock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How long did you stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 A week. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And then when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
 you lived with your parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I - I lived ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How long did you live with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I lived with them - I never left them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You lived with them all your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. We were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
 from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But when did you come to live in Clarement Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Now you've got that I lived in Clarement Road - er - I was born in Clarement Road - in Clarement Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But you did come back to Clarement Road later didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, af
ter me father died - I went to live off Eccles New Road - we left the house at the corporation yard - we had no need to leave it but - they didn't want us to leave - but - er - I wanted to get away from round there - I'd lived there all me life and I want
ed to get away. And we got a house off Ord Street in - er off Eccles New Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Howard Street off Eccles New Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - Zacharrias Street - we got a house and I was there over twenty years. 'Til we came up here - came back to the Height. And then 
I came .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Why did you leave Zacharrias Street and come to Clarement Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Came from Zacharrias Street. Well, me youngest daughter was working up here on Bolton Road at a grocers shop and - er - I thought if I can get a small house - you see, 
he'd had to - he had to retire from the stores when they were sixty-five. Well, some years before he finished work they got - er - employees superannuation going at the Pembleton Co-Op - well a lot of very young people - the younger end - they found out t
h
at some the older hands were getting the old age pension which is ten shillings a week then, and they were still working you see - they got their wages - 'course the Co-Op didn't pay good wages, you know, it was regular but they didn't pay big wages. Well
,
 when Ted was sixty-five he got the old age pension and he kept on work and he'd been working two years when they bought it in that they must all leave. Those that were sixty-five and over, they all had to retire. And they got - er - the superannuation th
en. 'Course it wasn't wa - like wages - it wasn't a big superannuation. Well, er - we came - we'd come up here because of Bessie - I wanted - I felt it was a long way for her from Eccles New Road every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was it a big house in Zacharrias Street - how many rooms was there in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Six. Yes - and with him having to finish work and only the superannuation and the rent had gone up - it was twelve shillings a week rent.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 That was a lot of money in those days wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 It was. And I thought if I could get a little house - er - with the lower rent it would help me a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your husband always work for the Co-Op?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He worked fourty-four years for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How old was he when you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He was thirty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He was older than you then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh he was seven years older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And you didn't work after marriage at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, I didn't work - good while before I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  - because of - I - kept house at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How many children did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Only two - I'd no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What years were they born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well Edna was born the first day of 1900.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And when was the other one born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - on a Good Friday - 18 - er - 1912.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So there was twelve years difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Twelve years between them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were they born at home or did you go in hospital?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, they were both born at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you know what to expect when they were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 There was nothing then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 They didn't tell you anything about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did you get on - did you have a doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes, I had a doctor - and the doctor - if I hadn't had a doctor over Edna I'd have died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How long were you in bed - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I was in bed over three weeks - and then I - I was bad. Oh I was - I had a bad abcess in me breast and ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you breast feed the baby yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did you have to feed them on in those days then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, you fed them on milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Just cows milk was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Cows milk - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your husband help you at all when the babies were born - how did you manage in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well it was - at night he used to get - they always wakened up about three o'clock in the morning - he'd get up and warm them a drink. Oh he was very good with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he help in the house too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, he didn't do a lot in the house - no - he'd wash the babies bottles, but not the nappies.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who did the housework then - did you have relatives or neighbours helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I used to plod along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You didn't have a nurse or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, I - er - over Edna I engaged - er - the doctor - our own doctor and - er - I engaged a person - she was a qualified midwife and it was a good job I had because the doctor wouldn't - well he said himself - he'd had to have had some practical help.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How long were you kept in bed in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 They kept - kept people in bed ten days. You got up the tenth day - but I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 If you needed advice who did you go to for help? Nowadays there are clinics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh there was nobody there - nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Suppose the baby cried a lot and you needed help who did you ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You - you had to manage the best way you could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you wake it for a feed or did you wait until it was ready for a feed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, it - they - they always used to seem to cry at one time. I got them that way you know - if you fed them regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What happened if it didn't seem hungry? And how long did you let it go on feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I didn't feed them off the breast. Yes - I think I used to put so much in the bottle you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When did your children first have solid food and when did you wean them.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - with - er - with Edna she was a - a very tiny baby - she was - and - er - I know 
the doctor said when he - of course he had to bring her - I didn't give birth to her - he brought her. I just remembered hearing him say to - this nurse - he says with all that struggling and pain for that bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You didn't have chloroform or anything in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. They didn't - you suffered it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What age did your children go on solid foods - do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - er - Edna I think she never had solid food 'til after she was twelve months old but ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did she take it easily or did she object?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, she seemed to fall in like. But Bessie was ready for solid food at six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And you gave it to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you think it did any harm to let a baby cry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 They used - some people did. I - no, I th
ink I tried to soothe them some way. But I remember Bessie at nine months old she sucked a pickled onion. She did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever have to punish them when they were naughty? When they were babies.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, they - they weren't naughty really. No, I couldn't say they ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was your husband fond of babies - did he have a lot to do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No, no, he - he loved them - he - he loved them but - I never - I have - since I've had time to think he - he seemed to love me - he loved me and he never let a - love for the babies overcome that you know - he was good to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he feed them or bath them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh he'd feed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He used to change their nappies and things - he did like them when they were tiny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh he liked them - he liked them - oh yes, he liked them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And he fed them in the night you said. Would he take them out on their own without you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, no, he didn't do much of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you always know what your husband earned? You know some people used to say my husband bring the wage packet home ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oh - no - I've heard people say it - no - mine didn't do that. No - he didn't bring his pocket home but he always gave me - I could depend on it and I had - er - we had our golden wedding - er - fif - were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  fifty-three years before he - when he died and from the day we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
 'til the day he died I never knew him to ask me for a ha'penny back. He gave me his wage and he kept perhaps just a few shillings for himself - of course at first he'd only be abl
e to keep perhaps half-a-crown. That - that had to do his pocket money for the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you talk it over how you'd spend the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh he never thought to. Oh never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You told me you lived at Trafalgar Square with your mother so it was the 
same number house and you lived with them as sort of relatives didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I lived with them because - er - they had to live there - the - the house was attached to the corporation yard you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But you and your husband went to live with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, we, yes, we lived with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you still do the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I did everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have any paid help when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No - only - no, no, I did everything - I did it for years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you make or mend clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, no I didn't do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you always buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 They were always - the men's clothes - I made plenty for myself and the children when I had Edna little I used to make - er - her things.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You had two children - Edna and who was the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Bessie. But there's twelve years between them. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were your clothes always new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, we didn't buy secondhand clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember where you bought them after you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I think - after I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  - you didn't buy clothes as often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How often did you buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When we needed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - that was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your husband ever mend them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Me father did for years when we were young but after - of course - no Ted never mended shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were they always new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh they - he always bought new shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember where the shoes were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well we bought them at the stores. He worked at the stores and I used to go in the club at the stores - the general club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 If you worked at the Co-Op wasn't there some rule that you had to spend so much with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No, I never heard of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your husband ever help you with jobs round the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, he'd wash up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He didn't help you with fires or decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He used to light the fire every morning and cook his own breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about the children - did they help you - did they have regular jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I never bothered to let - I never bothered them at all, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about your children - did you have a rule about bed time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh when they were little - oh yes they went to bed at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about when they were at school? Did they go to bed early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. They went to bed proper time. Well, when they got old enough they'd perhaps - I'd let them stay up 'til about eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Who put them to bed - did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I've done and their father's done it. Oh he did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he help them with dressing and undressing? And bathing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, he didn't - he didn't bother about that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he read to them or tell them stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He used - I'll tell you what he used - he didn't both
er much with Edna - because I me brother - me youngest brother lived at the other end of Trafalgar Square and Edna used to go and play with his children - you see she was - I had her for twelve years - she was like an only child and yet she wasn't brought
 up like an only child because she played with - er - me brothers children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your husband ever tell them stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh he, he used to tell them funny tales - I couldn't tell you now what they were. He was - he was humorous - he didn't like smutt
y - he never did like smut - anything smutty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he take them out on his own at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He - when Edna was little he took her out - on a Sunday morning perhaps for a walk in her - you know, in her pram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Suppose you went out, would he look after them while you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, they never seemed as if they wanted much looking after, you see, I always had me father and mother there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did you go on with sleeping arrangements now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh well, we had three bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes. And your mum and dad had one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
They had one and we had one and then when Edna was old enough to have a room to herself she had it. And then when we had Bessie of course Bessie went with Edna when she was old enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did you go on for bathing - had you got a bathroom at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Where did you bath - in the kitchen still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How often did you bath your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I used to bath them - I don't say they were bathed all over every night - I used to wash them all befo
re they - washed them before they went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And how often did they have clean clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Where were the meals eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Now you were another family living with your mother did you ever use another room for any occasion for eating in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, now and again we'd have a meal in the front room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about the cooking - did you still cook the same as your mother in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I cooked in the kitchen - you couldn't cook anywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And what about breakfast - now you were a big family how it was eaten. Did you all have it together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, Ted always cooked - got up and cooked his own. Oh he - I - he liked to cook his own breakfast. And he liked to have it to himself.
 He didn't like anybody in the morning - bothering him - no he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he cook a breakfast of did he just have toast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, he cooked bacon and - every morning - and sausage or egg or .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did he have on Sunday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh we - we - oh no - we lived - we lived very .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you all have bacon and eggs then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I never did have bacon - I wasn't fond - I wasn't - it didn't do for me some way - bacon in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When did you have your meal - later - the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No, I - no, I never bothered. I always cooked a dinner - a mid-day meal. Well, plain dinners - perhaps we used to have hot-pot or hash or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Something special on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, we got a joint at the weekend. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about evening meals when your children were little - do you remember what you used to have for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Tea? Oh I don't know - used - when Ted was at the stores I used - I often used to cook him a bit of something for his tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So, Ted got up and got his own breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, he always got his own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12128179\charrsid9916195 break}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 fast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And then did the rest of you have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Me father as a rule he had porridge in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So when you got up you had several different breakfasts to cook had you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes. And me mother she liked a bit of toasted cheese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So you had a lot of breakfast to prepare?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh we didn't bother - we just ........
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you make your own bread after you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I can't say I made it every week but I have made plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you make your own jam or pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I made - I made me own jam and pickles and - because me mother had always done it, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you bottle fruit or vegetable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I didn't bottle. Not ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you make wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about medicines - did you have your own favourite recipes? Or did you make medicines of any kind?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, I didn't - I don't know that we did - used - sometimes I'd try if I saw a recipe in a bo
ok I might try it for a bit of a cake or something like that, you know. I made my own wedding cake. Oh I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You didn't have a big wedding though did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You couldn't grow vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, no - no garden at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How about livestock - did you still keep hens after you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh - er - in the corporation yard - yes. Not in - not in our back yard. Oh no we never - we had cats and dogs, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you look after them or did your mother go on looking after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, I. No, I - didn't bother - used - we always had a cat or a couple of kittens and something like that and a dog - a little dog or two.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How many times a week did you have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Meat? Oh I think we had a bit of meat of some kind every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you eat much tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, there - there wasn't much tinned meat I think going then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever have to go short so that your husband and children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he have larger helpings of food than the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I don't know that he had - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were your children allowed to talk at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh we - we used to let them talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And could they choose anything they wanted after you'd cooked it or did you make them eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
I think - er - Edna seemed satisfied with anything - Edna did - but when Bessie was little she was a little choosy little beggar. And - well she wouldn't eat. I'll tell you what she did when - you'll laught at this - it was - I
 don't know whether the war was on - it would be at the time - the second war was on you know and - er - we were rationed for meat - you didn't get much meat you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was this the 1914 war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No - the - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you let them leave food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, I - yes - that - as I say Edna used to eat up some way - I never loaded - over loaded them - I never gave them more than they could eat - they could have more if they wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 If they wanted the salt were they allowed to help themselves or did they have to ask.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, they helped - it was there on the table, always.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you teach them to hold their knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes. I - I did teach them that. Well I - I liked - I liked to see them eat clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did they have to sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well I - I never had any trouble getting them to sit up to the table - when there was a meal on the table. Some - some people made the children stand. Oh no, I never did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you let them bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Toys? No. They never did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And could they leave the table when they wanted or had they to leave at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, no - they used to get up and .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And did you have regular places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, they didn't - perhaps they wouldn't all be there at once. You see Ted didn't come home to a dinner for years. He - he couldn't come home for his mid-day meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you always serve the meal or did your mother serve it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I served the dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What about the children - when they were too young to feed themselves what happened - did you have them in a special chair and who fed them?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - I - I fed them because - I never had them on my knee while I was having a meal. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 They didn't have a special high chair or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes - I had a high chair - a table chair for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How old were they when they came to the table do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh well, I can't remember that. I used to put them in the high chair to the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have special ideas about bringing them up - about was right and wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I tried to learn - to teach them to behave themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have any very special ideas about what was right and wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I - I - I used to talk to them when they were little and they'd talk back so when they got talking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you and your husband have the same ideas about bringing up children? And did you talk about it a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, he - he
 didn't - er - he was good to them. And he'd - er - he - er - well with Bessie - I think he - as I say Edna never was an only one - well she had everything for herself for twelve years but she never resented Bessie - she never resented her and girls of tw
elve might have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your mother help you with the children and did you ask her for advice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, they were very pleased you know - oh they were delighted with my children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you never go to your mother for advice? If they were ill or you were worried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No. I didn't - because - no - I had - I had to sort of do for myself with my mother being lame like she was. I - I had had to do such a lot for myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Can you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for your childr
en like showing affection or teaching them about safety or food or discipline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I don't know, I - never seemed to get to anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you think you could share their worries with them? Did you like them to bring their worries to you if they were ever worried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Either never brought any worries home - thank God.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did you expect them to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Because - er - Edna went - er - to Christchurch school, I told you, in the street, and it was the nat - the best school 
I think in Salford at the time and - er - and of course }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14768855\charrsid9916195 when Bessie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
 came she - she went to - er - Robert Hall Street - er - we lived - er - then off Eccles New Road, yo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12128179\charrsid9916195 u see, I'd left down Trafalgar S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 quare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What year did you leave Trafalgar Square. - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 The year? Er - 1915 - Bessie was three years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were you very strict with your children - had they to speak to you in certain ways
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I didn't let them answer back very much. But I'd no trouble with Edna - she never did answer back - Bessie would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you and your husband ever manage to get out - had you anyone to look after them while you went out at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When - no - we never went - didn't go out. No - he - he didn't bother - to tell you the truth he was too tired when he got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't know that they ever did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember what you brought them up to believe was important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I don't know - I think - Edna we
nt to she - when she was ever so little she went to St Bartholomews - Sunday school and church - she got - er - a little friend - er - schoolfriend but with Bessie - she - she wasn't like Edna some way and yet - they loved each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Suppose someone hurt them did you tell them to hit back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Er - no - I don't know that anybody ever did - hurt them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were there any children you stopped them playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, I never did that - I never - did that. And they could always - I tell you what
 - they used to bring all - their own friends - it was open house - oh yes, they could always bring their friends - always - I let them bring their friends. Oh yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Suppose they did something you didn't like - who punished them - did you or did your husband?
