\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I - perhaps I'd be sewing or knitting or - reading - mostly sewing and knitting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 When you did go out where did you go to? Just this pub you told me you used to go to on Saturdays or did you go somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, we didn't go anywhere else. But .......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How many evenings a week would your husband spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, the people next door - that lived next door when we lived in - er - Zacharrias Street, we got - er - like - friendly with them - I didn't know them - we didn't know them 'til w
e went to live there and - er - they used to - they used to come in our house at night and we'd play cards. The four of us. Because it was when Bessie was too little that we couldn't leave - we couldn't have left her at home by herself and Edna would be o
ut you see, and .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So you used to play cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh we played - for hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 With the neighbours - did you have friends in to play games?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Just the four - the - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You never made music or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, we played - 
we just played cards and then I'd make a cup of tea and we'd have a biscuit - a bit of cake or something and a cup of tea and Bessie would go to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 These were friends of both you and your husband were they - not just your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, we'd nev
er - we only got - friendly with them after we got - went to live there. And they took a fancy to Bessie - they - they were very fond of Bessie and - er - she was a little wildfire and they took a fancy to her and - er - we - they were real good friends. 
We were real good friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Could your friends and neighbours call in casually or did you like them to wait until you invited them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, no, if they came they came, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Both friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever have anyone to 
help you in the home - say you were ill - what happened - did relations or friends or neighbours help you in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, when we lived in Zacharrias Street - er - it was just the neighbours that - er - I don't say they came in - only that Mrs Heal
ey that lived next door - for weeks she cleaned the front and - er - cleaned the windows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 This was once when you were ill was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What happened when you had your babies - you were with your mother then of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, I was - I was a Trafalgar Square then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 After you went to Zacharrias Street was your mother still alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 She only lived three months after we went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did she live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes - she died with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 She care with you did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How many evenings a week did your husband spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Ted - he never - he didn't go out at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Never? Not to clubs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, he never went to clubs - no he never went to clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you belong to a savings club or a boot club or a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh he didn't believe in funeral clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Why?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Oooh - he didn't believe in them. I don't know - I don't think he - he'd been brought up at home, you see, I don't think they'd had any need for anything like that at 
his home. You see, his father was an architect and that - and had his own business - and he was - he was a very big man in the Masons - his father was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Your husband wasn't in the Masons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He wasn't in any clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well it - no
 he wasn't in any club. I used to go in stores club. And that was a different kind - no he didn't believe in these - er - insurance clubs - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he take part in any sport or any kind - walking, fishing, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12933843\charrsid9916195 rac}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, he was a cyclist. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he have a bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No, he didn't bet - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 After you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
 did you ever go to theatres, concert halls or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Occasionally, when - first I knew him - before we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  - not after - he never wanted to go - I think he'd - I don't know what it was. Of course you know he was seven years older than I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did either of you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I - my hobby was general housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have any garden at Zacharrias Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, we'd no garden there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have any interests outside the home - did you ever go out and enjoy yourself? On your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I've gone on picnics with - er - the Conservative Association.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So you did have interests of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I - I went to Belgium on
e weekend with them. Now - er - Ted didn't come - he wouldn't come and we went to - er - one year we went to - er - Edinburgh - now he came there with me. With the Conservative Association. And so did Mr Healy that lived next door to us - Mr and Mrs Heale
y - they - they came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was your home in Zacharrias Street rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever see your landlord? What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 George Henry Taylor - he was the - he was the landlord - that - he had - he had collectors you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You never saw the landlord himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Not after we took the house and .......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you have a struggle to make ends meet when you were first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, not when I was first }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  because I - I had the housekeeping to do and I had me father's money.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was your husband ever ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 My husband? Oh Lord - no - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you take an interest in politics? And what were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh well, I can't tell you anything - only I joined the Women's Conservative Association.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Why the Conservative Association? Why did you hold these views? Did you think the Conservatives were the best or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I - I felt it was at the time - I must have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your husband have the same ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he vote before 1919? Do you ever remember him voting in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He always voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you husband feel he had to vote for a certain party because he worked at the Co-op?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I'll tell you this much - he wasn't interested in Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he ever feel that he ought to do - did he feel under any pressure at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
He worked at the Co-op but I don't think he - er - I don't know what it was but - he didn't think it was - he thought it was - I'll tell you what it was - befor
e he worked at the Co-op he worked in - er - in a grocers shop and he saw so much of - er - chicken they called it - buying - er - having a weekly bill and - many a time it never got paid. And I think he thought that the Co-op had originated with seeing t
hat and that was why he went to the Co-op. The Co-op didn't believe in credit you know - they didn't believe in credit customers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But did he ever feel that he ought to vote Labour because he was in the Co-op.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He never did vote Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But did he feel he ought to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was he a member of a political party too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Just you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Me and Bessie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you take part in any political activity apart from at election times - what did you do with the Conservatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Me, oh I canvassed - I joined when - when Sir Montague Barlow put up for South Salford and he - he organized a branch of the women's Conservative Association - him and two sisters and they went round canvassing the members and I joined and that was the be
ginning of it. But - er - Ted never interfered with me - if I wanted to go to a meeting I went - he never went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you enjoy the political meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I used to like going.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did you feel before you got the vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Were you annoyed that the women didn't have the vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I felt that women who - women ought to have a vote as well as men - I had that feeling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did your husband think so too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't know whether he thought that or not - he never ever - he never used to talk about it. But he never stopped me going - never tried.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But you enjoyed politics and you thought the Conservatives were the right people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And yet you always worked for them and you went to all their meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes, I did, I went to lots of meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you vote immediately you got the vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes, as soon as ever we could we voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You voted the first time the women had the vote, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You used to play at card games, you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2703166\charrsid9916195 Newmarket}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
 - no. With - er - them two packs of cards. We have them now in the house. \{ILLEGIBLE\} - that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You used to go to the Conservative club meeting once a month? What did you do when you got there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh we used to ........
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 His father was an architect you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But your husband didn't want to go into the architecte business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, he didn't want it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He stayed at Grammar school until he was sixteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And his brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And he chose grocery you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, I think father told him that when he could manage a shop himself - er - there was money enough to set him up and - well when he came out of his time -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 He spent four years did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 For nothing. And he lived in because he couldn't get home from - er - Newton Heath you know - and - in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he ever tell you what it was like living in at a grocers shop? Did he ever talk about it to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, he never talked about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did he like it do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Then - er - well perhaps if he'd been older he mightn't have chosen that business, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Why, do you think he'd have changed his job later if he'd had the chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I think he would - he might have done
 - but - he wasn't the type really to have a business of his own. He'd do - he'd do the - he'd employ somebody and he'd do the work. He was one of that sort. If they didn't shape properly for him he'd have done the job himself. But he wouldn't have argued
 with anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 His brother became an architect in his father's business did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Not in the father's business - the father died, you see, and - er - Willie was - er - working at at builders in - er - Seedley - and when the father died he broke the house up because the sister had got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  the year before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 There were three of them were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes. There were three of them. But the father kept - he gave them a good education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What did the sister do - did she ever go out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, she never went out to work - never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Even though they had a housekeeper she stayed at home, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, they had a housekeeper 'til she was old enough to take charge of the house. And then she did it 'til she got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you think your husband ever regretted not becoming an architect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No, I don't think he ever had any leaning that way at all but Willie had. His brother and that - he had - and - er - he played the piano a lot too, Willie did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And he went to a builders did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And he worked at a builders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Was this sort of serving an apprenticeship before he became an architect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't think Willie ever really qualified properly because the father died and he - he worked - Willie was working and I think 
when the father died it sort of broke them all up some way and - er - er - Ted was working at a grocers shop down Ordsall Lane when his father died - he - like was out of his time - and - er - how old was he - he wasn't really old enough to have a shop of
 his own. And then when the father died of course that ended it. And then he went - he got work at he went to the stores because they had more settled hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What were the hours when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  - do you remember? Were they long hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 They were. They worked 'til eight o'clock on a Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 From what time in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Er - I don't know whether it was eight or quarter past - I forget. Oh yes, they - worked 'til eight on a Monday, seven on a Tuesday - er - half past twelve on a Wednesday - they had half a day - Thursday was eight - Friday was nine and Saturday was eight.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 So you didn't have such life did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Now then. Well, soon after I knew him - er - they got an hour knocked off on a Saturday - they closed at seven. So that was a big godsend.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Of course all the shops kept open very late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, they all kept open.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember them auctioning meat for instance if they had any left over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever watch it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 I don't know that I
 ever saw it. Why, they used to auction butchers meat on Eccles New Road - er - on Regent Road at Walkers - near Cross Lane. And they used to auction parcels at night on a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Sand you used to have to take the parcel even if you didn't know what was in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Yes. Because I - I know a niece of mine that bought many a parcel - I never did I never saw it - I never went. We lived in Zacharrias Street but I never went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you see poverty round Zacharrias Street when you were living there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No. The - no - they seemed like - er - like working people they were round but they weren't poor - not the poor you know that you'd call poor. They perhaps were poor - they didn't - er - I mean to say they - they'd never more than they needed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What was the difference - it wasn't very far away was it - well ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, it wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, what was the difference between the poor you saw as a child in Ordsall Lane and the poor that you saw in Zaccharrias Street - do you remember the difference between the two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, in Zacharrias Street - well I was - I was one of them - er - Ted didn't get a great big killing wage but there were a few of the men in that street who did - I know the - the man next door to us that we were friendly with - he wa
s - er - a manager at Westmacotts the chemist - you know that - well he was the manager - they had a mineral water works - where they made mineral waters - soft drinks you know, minerals and soda water and he was the manager there. Now Mrs Healey his wife
 - he used to bring his wage packet home and give it her - every week - he never opened it. Now then. She was his second wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Where they were poor though ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 In Zacharrias Street, the people who worked - what was the actual difference - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, they didn't let you know that - that - you'd know yourself that they were - they'd nothing to spare - you'd know that if you saw them shopping - I dare say they've seen it with me. But they got - perhaps got a weekly wage -
 we got a weekly wage always - nearly always - all the women in the street - we got a weekly wage off our husbands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you know anything about the Guardians in those days - did you know anybody who went and how they treated them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember the work house in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh, I remember the work house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Tell me what you remember about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well, I don't know anything really - because I never had anything to do with it - only looking at it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You remember the building itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh I remember the building.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 But you never knew anybody who went in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No. No, I didn't - no. I used to see the - whatsits at night on Eccles New Road - at a little door - a little gate that there was - a little gate - there were t
ramps I think going in for a nights lodging and I believe they got their - a cup of cocoa or something and a piece of bread and then they got the same in the morning. I think that was what they got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And this was at the work house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 And the
n, after they got their breakfast as they called it they had to do so much work - breaking stones - or doing something. Before they were let out. Er - sort of earning a bit for what they'd had. They'd get a nights lodgings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Do you remember the old peo
ple who were in the workhouse - did you ever see them when you were young? Was there a workhouse on Oldfield Road near where you lived
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 On - er - Eccles Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 On Oldfield Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh no, it wasn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Where was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 It was on Eccles New Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did you ever see any of the old people who were in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
No, I don't know that I did. No, I - I - I've heard them say that they weren't very generous, you know, at helping the - anyone that was left a widow. I don't know - well, they reckoned it was ratepayer's money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Did widows get any help at all when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
I don't know what they got. I know one - er - I remember - I can remember when - er - where did we live then - oh it was before we went into Zacharrias Street I 
think - a bit before - there was a - er - a girl and her husband died - she - she had one baby - one little child and I think she was having another when he died - and she was - a dressmaker really - a very - a very - a nice girl and they'd got a nice lit
t
le home and - er - he died - he took pneumonia and - er - she went to the Guardians - it was then - they called them Guardians and they said they'd come and have a look at her house. She - she had a nice little home and I believe somebody came and had a l
ook - one of the Guardians - er - two of them - and they told her before they let - gave her anything to sell her sideboard. And she'd been left a young widow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Widows must have been worse off then than they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Oh they were. They were. And she was only a young woman - she was only about twenty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 How did they go on in those days if they were left a widow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Well - er - she was a dressmaker and her mother lived near - not far away her mother lived and she used to take the children a
nd her mother had them and she went out to work. She said she couldn't break her home up like that. Yes, they told her to - she - she wasn't in wasn't - to sell her sideboard.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 What do you think was the difference in your upbringing as a child and the
 way you bought your children up - do you remember a big difference in ideas - did you change your ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 No, I - I was always happy because I - I never was in want you see - I never wanted for anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 You don't think the discipline was much different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
We never had a lot of luxury but we had all we wanted - all we needed rather and of course I - it was the same with my children. We had - they had what we needed and that was all - we couldn't save anything. Oh no - you couldn't save.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 Weren't you afraid of your husband ever coming out of work or anything? Did it worry you a great deal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2454056 EM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
Well, it would have done perhaps if he'd had a job where he was on piece work or or a place where he didn't get paid for holidays - at the stores t
hey did get paid for holidays, you know. Oh yes. Oh yes, they always got - er - their - their holi - I know when we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 
 they didn't give them their holiday pay 'til they went back - the week after. That - that was the year we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3305828 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195  - they d
idn't get their wages 'til they went back - the Monday following - they only had a week and they got their wages then when they went back. Well, after that year they began to give it them the - the night they finished - on the Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14228208 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid936107\charrsid9916195 The Co-op must have been the first to start holidays with pay in this area?
